{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17638826","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17638826"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:59:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:59:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17737"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17737","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17737"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.43,0.17,0.22,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10451"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75663"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10451","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10451"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17737"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61181"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"449"},{"type":"tags","id":"1189"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"4340"},{"type":"tags","id":"4522"},{"type":"tags","id":"4828"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"6625"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24402"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24404"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75663"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic feeling unwell. She reports fatigue and has noticed her periods have been irregular. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears pale. Her pulse rate is 90 beats per minute, blood pressure is 110/70 mmHg, respiratory rate 14 per minute, SpO2 99% in room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. A full blood count reveals haemoglobin of 105 g/L (115-155).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following tests is most appropriate to do during this visit?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Serum progesterone level","Urine pregnancy test","Complete blood count","Serum beta-hCG test","Pelvic ultrasound"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate initial test to confirm pregnancy is a \u003Cstrong\u003Eurine pregnancy test\u003C/strong\u003E. This test detects the presence of human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG) in the urine, which is produced shortly after a fertilised egg attaches to the uterine lining. It is a quick, non-invasive, and cost-effective method for confirming pregnancy. All women of child-bearing age should be investigated for pregnancy as part of differential diagnosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eserum beta-hCG test\u003C/strong\u003E is more sensitive and can detect pregnancy earlier when compared with a urine beta-hCG. It is typically used when a more precise measurement of hCG is needed, such as in cases of suspected ectopic pregnancy or when the urine test is inconclusive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epelvic ultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E is not the first-line test for confirming pregnancy. It is used to assess the viability of the pregnancy, determine gestational age, or investigate complications once pregnancy is confirmed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ecomplete blood count\u003C/strong\u003E is useful for evaluating anaemia, as seen in this patient, but it does reflect pregnancy status.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum progesterone level\u003C/strong\u003E is not used to confirm pregnancy. It may be measured in certain cases to assess the viability of a pregnancy or in the evaluation of recurrent pregnancy loss.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A urine pregnancy test is a quick and non-invasive method to confirm or rule-out pregnancy.","Serum beta-hCG testing is more sensitive and can detect pregnancy earlier than urine tests, and are sometimes required to inform diagnosis or management","Anaemia in a woman of child-bearing age could be related to pregnancy, among many other differential diagnoses"],"references":["DeLaney M, Wood L. Urine pregnancy testing: When does no mean maybe? J Am Coll Emerg Physicians Open. 2021 Sep 28;2(5):e12567. doi: 10.1002/emp2.12567. PMID: 34611652; PMCID: PMC8479369.","Chard T. Pregnancy tests: a review. Hum Reprod. 1992 May;7(5):701-10. doi: 10.1093/oxfordjournals.humrep.a137722. PMID: 1639991.","Priyadarshini S, Manas F, Prabhu S. False Negative Urine Pregnancy Test: Hook Effect Revealed. Cureus. 2022 Mar 2;14(3):e22779. doi: 10.7759/cureus.22779. PMID: 35371840; PMCID: PMC8971111."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61181"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17737"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61181","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61181"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-30T13:30:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-30T13:30:52+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10451"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75663"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings",